        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-7">
            <div class="text-block mb-50">
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20 font-weight-bold color-secondary">
                Expertise in Advanced Laparoscopic Procedures
              </p>
              <div class="video-banner-layout3 bg-overlay mb-50">
                <img src="/assets/images/banners/14.jpg" alt="Laparoscopic Surgery" loading="lazy" width="800" height="450">
                <a class="video__btn video__btn-white popup-video" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nrJtHemSPW4">
                  <div class="video__player">
                    <i class="fa fa-play"></i>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div><!-- /.video-banner -->
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our surgical team at SALi is highly skilled in performing complex laparoscopic surgeries. This minimally invasive approach uses small incisions and a camera to perform procedures, leading to less pain, reduced scarring, and a quicker return to normal activities.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                We perform a wide range of laparoscopic procedures, including cholecystectomy (gallbladder removal), liver resections, and pancreatic surgery. Our commitment to using the latest surgical technology ensures the best outcomes for our patients.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Benefits of Laparoscopic Surgery</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Smaller Incisions:</strong> Typically 4-5 small cuts (0.5-1cm) instead of one large incision.</li>
                <li><strong>Less Pain:</strong> Significantly reduced post-operative pain compared to open surgery.</li>
                <li><strong>Faster Recovery:</strong> Most patients return home within 1-3 days and resume normal activities within 2 weeks.</li>
                <li><strong>Reduced Scarring:</strong> Minimal cosmetic impact with tiny scars that fade over time.</li>
                <li><strong>Lower Infection Risk:</strong> Smaller wounds mean reduced risk of surgical site infections.</li>
                <li><strong>Shorter Hospital Stay:</strong> Less recovery time needed in the hospital.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Laparoscopic Procedures We Perform</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Laparoscopic Cholecystectomy:</strong> Gold standard for gallstone removal and gallbladder disease. Our surgeons perform hundreds of these procedures annually with excellent outcomes.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Laparoscopic Liver Resection:</strong> Removal of liver tumors or cysts using minimally invasive techniques. Suitable for selected patients with benign or malignant liver lesions.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Laparoscopic Common Bile Duct Exploration:</strong> Treatment of bile duct stones that cannot be removed by ERCP.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Diagnostic Laparoscopy:</strong> Minimally invasive examination of the abdomen to diagnose conditions and assess disease extent.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Advanced Laparoscopic Techniques</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our surgeons are trained in advanced laparoscopic techniques including robotic-assisted surgery for complex cases. We use high-definition 3D imaging systems and specialized instruments to perform intricate procedures with precision. Intraoperative ultrasound helps identify small lesions and guide surgical decisions.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Patient Selection and Safety</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Not all patients are candidates for laparoscopic surgery. We carefully evaluate each patient's condition, medical history, and anatomy to determine if laparoscopic surgery is appropriate. Factors considered include tumor size and location, previous abdominal surgeries, bleeding disorders, and overall health status. If laparoscopic surgery is not suitable, we discuss alternative approaches including open surgery or other treatment options.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Post-Operative Care</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                After laparoscopic surgery, patients are monitored in our recovery area. Most can walk and take liquids within hours of surgery. Pain is managed with oral medications, and drains (if placed) are typically removed within 1-2 days. Follow-up appointments ensure proper healing, and our surgical team remains available for any concerns during recovery.
              </p>
